1
00:00:06,230 --> 00:00:07,980
You...

2
00:00:09,980 --> 00:00:11,480
Are you leaving?

3
00:00:20,522 --> 00:00:22,480
Do you want me to stay?

4
00:00:26,772 --> 00:00:30,938
You can leave, but pay me back first.

5
00:00:31,063 --> 00:00:32,855
And don't forget every
cent of the interest.

6
00:00:36,813 --> 00:00:39,147
Hey, Wooju.

7
00:00:39,272 --> 00:00:40,522
Yeah?

8
00:00:42,522 --> 00:00:47,563
When we're talking money, call me Boss.

9
00:01:12,938 --> 00:01:14,855
Teach me how to sing.

10
00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:15,980
You play the piano?

11
00:01:16,063 --> 00:01:18,522
I can play anything after hearing it once.

12
00:01:39,522 --> 00:01:40,897
How is that possible?

13
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:44,438
Like I said, I just
hear it and I've got it.

14
00:01:47,897 --> 00:01:51,813
♪ Fly me to the moon ♪

15
00:01:51,938 --> 00:01:57,105
♪ Let me play among the stars ♪

16
00:01:58,188 --> 00:02:01,647
♪ Let me see what spring is like ♪

17
00:02:01,772 --> 00:02:06,772
♪ On Jupiter and Mars ♪

18
00:02:08,522 --> 00:02:11,480
♪ In other words ♪

19
00:02:12,438 --> 00:02:14,272
♪ Hold my hand ♪

20
00:02:17,730 --> 00:02:21,355
♪ In other words ♪

21
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:24,313
♪ Baby, kiss me ♪

22
00:02:29,313 --> 00:02:32,563
♪ Fill my heart with song ♪

23
00:02:32,688 --> 00:02:37,938
♪ And let me sing forevermore ♪

24
00:02:38,938 --> 00:02:42,438
♪ You are all I long for ♪

25
00:02:42,563 --> 00:02:47,480
♪ All I worship and adore ♪

26
00:02:48,897 --> 00:02:51,897
♪ In other words ♪

27
00:02:52,022 --> 00:02:56,813
♪ Please be true ♪

28
00:02:57,313 --> 00:03:01,147
♪ In other words ♪

29
00:03:01,272 --> 00:03:04,480
♪ I love you ♪

30
00:03:08,522 --> 00:03:09,980
Whoa!

31
00:03:12,813 --> 00:03:14,355
You scared me.

32
00:03:14,855 --> 00:03:17,438
Didn't I tell you I was a prince?

33
00:03:17,563 --> 00:03:19,022
I did it again.

34
00:03:19,938 --> 00:03:21,313
Stop talking nonsense.

35
00:03:27,272 --> 00:03:29,855
♪ Fly me to the moon ♪

36
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:33,730
♪ Let me play among the stars ♪

37
00:03:34,355 --> 00:03:36,813
♪ Let me see what spring is like ♪

38
00:03:36,938 --> 00:03:40,980
♪ On Jupiter and Mars ♪

39
00:03:41,772 --> 00:03:43,438
♪ In other words ♪

40
00:03:44,563 --> 00:03:48,772
♪ Hold my hand ♪

41
00:03:48,897 --> 00:03:54,855
♪ In other words ♪

42
00:03:54,980 --> 00:03:58,438
♪ Baby, kiss me ♪

43
00:04:09,772 --> 00:04:11,397
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

44
00:04:13,980 --> 00:04:15,438
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

45
00:04:17,897 --> 00:04:19,563
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

46
00:04:21,688 --> 00:04:23,563
(Q / Q)

47
00:04:25,772 --> 00:04:27,605
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

48
00:04:32,397 --> 00:04:37,188
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 7)

49
00:04:38,897 --> 00:04:39,897
(Fly Me to the Moon)

50
00:04:43,022 --> 00:04:45,522
Hachi, congratulations.

51
00:04:46,022 --> 00:04:47,272
Is it finally fixed?

52
00:04:47,397 --> 00:04:49,563
I think this device will be restored soon.

53
00:04:49,688 --> 00:04:52,230
Communication on Earth
will be possible tonight.

54
00:04:52,355 --> 00:04:53,563
Oh.

55
00:04:56,647 --> 00:04:58,397
Will you be back soon?

56
00:04:59,022 --> 00:05:02,772
Yes, I can finally say goodbye
to this dump planet Earth.

57
00:05:03,855 --> 00:05:05,855
I like Earth quite a bit.

58
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:06,980
Don't you?

59
00:05:07,105 --> 00:05:08,522
Well...

60
00:05:08,813 --> 00:05:09,980
Hachi.

61
00:05:10,105 --> 00:05:11,897
I have something I wanna give you.

62
00:05:13,188 --> 00:05:16,063
A token of our friendship.

63
00:05:16,688 --> 00:05:18,605
C'mon, let's try it on.

64
00:05:18,730 --> 00:05:20,855
How should... how should I...?

65
00:05:20,980 --> 00:05:22,230
Look there.

66
00:05:22,355 --> 00:05:23,855
I'll put it on you.

67
00:05:28,938 --> 00:05:29,938
Wow.

68
00:05:30,438 --> 00:05:32,397
It looks good on you.

69
00:05:32,522 --> 00:05:33,813
Thanks.

70
00:05:35,647 --> 00:05:38,230
Don't forget me when you go back home, OK?

71
00:05:41,105 --> 00:05:44,647
By any chance... do you wanna go with me?

72
00:05:45,813 --> 00:05:48,938
No, I have to stay with the princess.

73
00:05:49,813 --> 00:05:51,355
She needs me.

74
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,230
Hey, I'll see you soon, okay?

75
00:05:56,355 --> 00:05:57,605
Okay.

76
00:06:02,147 --> 00:06:04,605
Did you learn to bake from my dad?

77
00:06:04,730 --> 00:06:06,063
Yeah.

78
00:06:06,313 --> 00:06:11,397
I came here to see your dad.

79
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:14,480
Why did you want to see him?

80
00:06:15,897 --> 00:06:20,730
He was my only friend.

81
00:06:21,230 --> 00:06:25,605
My family, and my mentor.

82
00:06:25,730 --> 00:06:30,063
He always took such good care of me.

83
00:06:32,313 --> 00:06:38,272
But how could you not know he passed away?

84
00:06:41,563 --> 00:06:43,897
We lost touch a long time ago.

85
00:06:45,772 --> 00:06:48,313
He just left a letter and vanished.

86
00:06:50,605 --> 00:06:52,980
Went somewhere far away.

87
00:06:58,355 --> 00:07:02,980
I only heard later that he got married.

88
00:07:05,272 --> 00:07:08,272
How did you know I was his son?

89
00:07:17,647 --> 00:07:19,522
It was obvious the moment I saw you.

90
00:07:20,813 --> 00:07:22,980
You look exactly like him.

91
00:07:30,438 --> 00:07:34,772
Why didn't you say so earlier?

92
00:07:34,897 --> 00:07:36,855
Would you have believed me?

93
00:07:37,605 --> 00:07:39,813
Even if I told you now,

94
00:07:39,938 --> 00:07:42,105
you still wouldn't believe me, right?

95
00:07:45,730 --> 00:07:48,772
That's because you're
always saying weird things.

96
00:07:50,938 --> 00:07:53,563
Your dad's soul must have brought me here.

97
00:07:55,522 --> 00:08:00,230
I missed him so much,

98
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,188
that's how I found you.

99
00:08:25,730 --> 00:08:27,105
What are you doing?

100
00:08:27,230 --> 00:08:28,480
A kiss.

101
00:08:30,230 --> 00:08:31,397
A kiss?

102
00:08:31,522 --> 00:08:32,313
Yeah.

103
00:08:32,438 --> 00:08:34,188
Who kisses like that?

104
00:08:36,438 --> 00:08:37,897
Well...

105
00:08:38,730 --> 00:08:41,105
That's how we do it back home.

106
00:08:41,230 --> 00:08:45,438
Hey, since you're on Earth now,

107
00:08:48,272 --> 00:08:50,063
do it the Earth way.

108
00:09:33,147 --> 00:09:34,438
Officer Shin.

109
00:09:34,563 --> 00:09:35,022
Yes?

110
00:09:35,147 --> 00:09:36,647
The report on last night's case,

111
00:09:36,772 --> 00:09:37,813
is it finished?

112
00:09:37,938 --> 00:09:39,188
Just a second.

113
00:09:42,105 --> 00:09:43,438
Here it is.

114
00:09:46,105 --> 00:09:47,397
Officer Shin.

115
00:09:47,522 --> 00:09:48,647
Yes, sir?

116
00:09:48,772 --> 00:09:53,313
That... UFO... alien-related club,

117
00:09:53,438 --> 00:09:54,772
did you quit it?

118
00:09:55,063 --> 00:09:58,313
Yes. I decided to drop any hobbies that

119
00:09:58,438 --> 00:09:59,438
interfere with work.

120
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:01,397
Okay, good. That's better.

121
00:10:01,522 --> 00:10:03,105
That's the way.

122
00:10:22,688 --> 00:10:23,897
A little lower here.

123
00:10:24,022 --> 00:10:25,188
Ugh...

124
00:10:27,355 --> 00:10:28,480
Hurry up!

125
00:10:28,605 --> 00:10:29,688
Ouch.

126
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,772
Seriously.

127
00:10:33,980 --> 00:10:34,480
Hey...

128
00:10:34,605 --> 00:10:36,313
Turn around.

129
00:10:38,688 --> 00:10:39,980
Wait.

130
00:10:40,105 --> 00:10:42,063
Oh, for heaven's sake.

131
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:53,438
He's coming.

132
00:10:56,563 --> 00:10:58,188
Mina, trust me on this.

133
00:11:01,063 --> 00:11:04,105
I bought this for my
partner, but you take it.

134
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:05,688
Why? We haven't even left yet.

135
00:11:05,813 --> 00:11:08,313
I'll explain later. Just put it on.

136
00:11:09,563 --> 00:11:10,772
What's with the sunglasses?

137
00:11:10,897 --> 00:11:14,230
I was in the dark for too
long. My eyes are sensitive.

138
00:11:14,355 --> 00:11:16,313
Has anything been inconvenient lately?

139
00:11:16,431 --> 00:11:17,138
Of course it has...

140
00:11:17,169 --> 00:11:19,272
Not at all! You've taken
such good care of us.

141
00:11:19,397 --> 00:11:20,272
Everything's been fine.

142
00:11:20,397 --> 00:11:22,813
Hmm... I've been thinking.

143
00:11:22,938 --> 00:11:25,855
And I'm curious how much you actually know.

144
00:11:28,063 --> 00:11:29,897
You're aliens, aren't you?

145
00:11:31,313 --> 00:11:32,897
What about it?

146
00:11:33,022 --> 00:11:35,563
Are you here to arrest me? I
haven't done anything wrong.

147
00:11:35,688 --> 00:11:36,813
What law did I break?

148
00:11:36,938 --> 00:11:38,605
I'm a legal citizen here.

149
00:11:38,730 --> 00:11:41,897
And I run a legitimate business.

150
00:11:42,022 --> 00:11:45,522
What is your real purpose on Earth?

151
00:11:48,980 --> 00:11:49,688
Secretary Lee.

152
00:11:49,813 --> 00:11:51,188
Yes, Chairman.

153
00:12:10,105 --> 00:12:12,897
Oh my god! Run!

154
00:12:13,022 --> 00:12:14,355
Hurry... damn it.

155
00:12:18,730 --> 00:12:20,272
(Operation: Alien Extermination)

156
00:12:23,980 --> 00:12:26,813
Is this where Woo-hyuk grew up?

157
00:12:26,938 --> 00:12:29,188
Yes, I grew up here.

158
00:12:29,313 --> 00:12:34,605
I had lots of friends, and the
director took care of me like a mother.

159
00:12:34,730 --> 00:12:36,022
Woo-hyuk.

160
00:12:37,063 --> 00:12:39,438
- Hello, Director.
- Oh, come on in.

161
00:12:39,563 --> 00:12:42,147
- How have you been?
- Oh, thanks for coming all this way.

162
00:12:51,397 --> 00:12:54,157
(Operation: Alien Extermination)
Here is the list of confirmed aliens.

163
00:12:54,188 --> 00:12:55,605
Wow, there are so many.

164
00:12:55,730 --> 00:12:56,897
Yes, and...

165
00:12:57,522 --> 00:12:59,147
The aliens' first target

166
00:12:59,272 --> 00:13:02,397
is to activate the device inside
the Wooju Bakery building.

167
00:13:02,522 --> 00:13:03,914
What do you mean, activate the building?

168
00:13:03,938 --> 00:13:05,813
It looks like an ordinary building,

169
00:13:05,938 --> 00:13:10,188
but it's actually a
special device for aliens.

170
00:13:10,313 --> 00:13:11,188
Wait, hold on.

171
00:13:11,313 --> 00:13:12,147
What's wrong?

172
00:13:12,272 --> 00:13:12,897
Officer Sin.

173
00:13:13,022 --> 00:13:14,605
We shouldn't be handling this alone.

174
00:13:14,730 --> 00:13:18,897
Should we get the other
officers to look at this?

175
00:13:19,938 --> 00:13:21,230
Ah...

176
00:13:21,355 --> 00:13:23,647
Your mother seems like a wonderful person.

177
00:13:27,688 --> 00:13:31,688
I've never called her 'mother', though.

178
00:13:32,813 --> 00:13:34,147
Woo-hyuk.

179
00:13:38,105 --> 00:13:40,563
Do you think love is only about giving?

180
00:13:40,772 --> 00:13:42,563
Accepting love is also a form of love.

181
00:13:50,647 --> 00:13:51,980
Hmm?

182
00:13:52,438 --> 00:13:53,730
Officer Shin.

183
00:13:54,480 --> 00:13:56,105
I'm off today, though.

184
00:13:56,230 --> 00:13:57,230
Hey, senior.

185
00:13:57,272 --> 00:13:59,605
Please, listen to my troubles.

186
00:14:00,022 --> 00:14:00,772
What?

187
00:14:00,897 --> 00:14:02,105
Today...

188
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:04,980
is the most important day of my life.

189
00:14:05,105 --> 00:14:06,855
- It's so hot.
- No, that's not it.

190
00:14:06,980 --> 00:14:08,539
I was supposed to go to the movies today.

191
00:14:08,563 --> 00:14:09,688
Can't we do this tomorrow?

192
00:14:09,813 --> 00:14:11,397
Or you can just tell me over the phone.

193
00:14:11,522 --> 00:14:15,522
No, I need to see you in
person and tell you myself.

194
00:14:15,647 --> 00:14:18,022
Please, as a favor to your junior.

195
00:14:18,813 --> 00:14:21,022
Please, just listen.

196
00:14:21,563 --> 00:14:23,397
Fine, I'm on my way.

197
00:14:28,438 --> 00:14:33,730
Chairman, Officer Lee is furious.
He wants to wipe them all out.

198
00:14:34,230 --> 00:14:35,550
Secretary Lee, what do you think?

199
00:14:35,647 --> 00:14:37,022
I agree.

200
00:14:37,147 --> 00:14:39,813
I don't think there's any
reason to keep them around.

201
00:14:41,938 --> 00:14:44,605
The old owner of that bakery...

202
00:14:45,105 --> 00:14:45,897
What about him?

203
00:14:46,022 --> 00:14:48,147
How did he end up on Earth?

204
00:14:49,355 --> 00:14:51,063
Do you, perhaps, know?

205
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:52,855
What do you mean by that...

206
00:14:52,980 --> 00:14:55,438
He was the closest person to the King.

207
00:14:55,563 --> 00:14:58,230
Why would he flee to Earth?

208
00:14:59,813 --> 00:15:02,355
How should I know that information?

209
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:04,063
I'll be taking my leave.

210
00:15:14,230 --> 00:15:17,563
There's still... the accomplices and
the next steps for the investigation.

211
00:15:17,688 --> 00:15:18,688
I'll report back to you.

212
00:15:18,813 --> 00:15:22,313
So you're saying aliens came to
Earth to harvest vital resources?

213
00:15:22,438 --> 00:15:23,914
And they're still plotting a conspiracy?

214
00:15:23,938 --> 00:15:27,772
And the leader of these
aliens is Lee Seong-yong?

215
00:15:27,897 --> 00:15:29,980
Yes, that's right...

216
00:15:30,105 --> 00:15:32,230
Are you really expecting
us to believe this?

217
00:15:32,355 --> 00:15:33,397
It's all true!

218
00:15:33,522 --> 00:15:36,063
Officer Shin and I risked
our lives to uncover this.

219
00:15:36,188 --> 00:15:37,522
I'm not making this up.

220
00:15:37,647 --> 00:15:41,855
Do you think I can I apply
for witness protection?

221
00:15:43,313 --> 00:15:45,272
You just said you were
an alien, didn't you?

222
00:15:45,397 --> 00:15:46,730
Uh...

223
00:15:46,855 --> 00:15:50,730
The laws of the Republic of Korea
mandate full witness protection.

224
00:15:50,855 --> 00:15:51,605
Ah...

225
00:15:51,730 --> 00:15:53,605
I'll handle it.

226
00:15:57,230 --> 00:15:58,355
Senior.

227
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:01,147
You don't actually believe him, do you?

228
00:16:01,272 --> 00:16:06,105
Woo-hyuk, don't worry. I'll just
shoot him and be done with it.

229
00:16:12,605 --> 00:16:13,605
Senior.

230
00:16:14,397 --> 00:16:15,563
What's wrong with you?

231
00:16:15,688 --> 00:16:19,813
I believe everything Officer Shin found.

232
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:25,063
And I believe this alien witness, too.

233
00:16:27,063 --> 00:16:29,063
Because I'm an alien as well.

234
00:16:36,980 --> 00:16:41,647
Do we really have to use a cart
to move something this high-tech?

235
00:16:41,772 --> 00:16:45,022
The Chairman is rushing us,
so we have to get it there fast.

236
00:16:47,063 --> 00:16:49,980
That's strange. Why is this
cart so hard to push today?

237
00:16:56,730 --> 00:16:59,272
Hey! Get out of here, you jerk!

238
00:16:59,397 --> 00:16:59,938
Get lost!

239
00:17:00,063 --> 00:17:01,063
Move it.

240
00:17:01,188 --> 00:17:01,980
Get out of the way.

241
00:17:02,105 --> 00:17:03,522
Move.

242
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:04,647
Get out now!

243
00:17:08,397 --> 00:17:11,688
Wow, this smells just like home.

244
00:17:11,813 --> 00:17:13,313
Hey, try some.

245
00:17:13,730 --> 00:17:14,730
Ah...

246
00:17:14,855 --> 00:17:16,664
This is the first time I've
smelled a scent like home, boss.

247
00:17:16,688 --> 00:17:20,105
Sir, the bread must be
paid for before eating.

248
00:17:21,355 --> 00:17:22,813
Here.

249
00:17:26,563 --> 00:17:29,397
Sir, this is too much.

250
00:17:29,522 --> 00:17:31,897
Keep it all. No need for change.

251
00:17:32,022 --> 00:17:34,063
Boss, why did you give him so much?

252
00:17:34,188 --> 00:17:36,980
We won't be needing Earth
money for much longer anyway.

253
00:17:37,105 --> 00:17:37,980
That makes sense.

254
00:17:38,105 --> 00:17:40,855
Yeah, Earth was never really
a place for us to stay anyway...

255
00:17:40,980 --> 00:17:42,272
Good grief.

256
00:17:42,397 --> 00:17:43,730
Where's the owner of this place?

257
00:17:43,855 --> 00:17:44,397
Our boss?

258
00:17:44,522 --> 00:17:46,772
I'm the owner. What's going on here?

259
00:17:46,897 --> 00:17:48,147
The owner?

260
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:51,605
You're the owner here?

261
00:17:51,730 --> 00:17:53,438
It's true, I'm the owner.

262
00:17:54,105 --> 00:17:55,688
Are you crazy...

263
00:17:57,355 --> 00:17:58,438
You're the owner?

264
00:17:58,563 --> 00:18:01,563
I mean... I work hard
like I'm the owner here.

265
00:18:02,063 --> 00:18:03,438
Are you the owner here?

266
00:18:03,563 --> 00:18:04,603
Yes... is there a problem?

267
00:18:04,688 --> 00:18:06,938
We're taking over this building.

268
00:18:07,063 --> 00:18:09,772
I happen to have a much
bigger and nicer place nearby.

269
00:18:09,897 --> 00:18:13,772
I can help you move there. And
there're issues about moving, right?

270
00:18:13,897 --> 00:18:15,772
We'll even cover the moving costs.

271
00:18:15,897 --> 00:18:17,188
We'll take care of everything.

272
00:18:17,313 --> 00:18:19,039
How about it? That's a
pretty good deal, right?

273
00:18:19,063 --> 00:18:19,897
So, Prince.

274
00:18:20,022 --> 00:18:21,563
We done being slaves here, too.

275
00:18:21,688 --> 00:18:23,730
Wooju, let's sell this place.

276
00:18:23,855 --> 00:18:26,022
Let's open a shop in a bigger place.

277
00:18:26,147 --> 00:18:27,438
No.

278
00:18:27,563 --> 00:18:28,980
Why not?

279
00:18:33,438 --> 00:18:35,063
The landlord is here, too.

280
00:18:36,938 --> 00:18:39,688
Grandpa, do we really have to move?

281
00:18:41,522 --> 00:18:42,938
Sigh...

282
00:18:43,063 --> 00:18:44,980
It seems it would be better to move.

283
00:18:45,105 --> 00:18:46,522
How can that be?

284
00:18:47,355 --> 00:18:49,875
The reason I opened this bakery
here is because of my father...

285
00:18:50,188 --> 00:18:52,355
I just wanted to keep
my father's bakery going.

286
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:54,438
You're the son of the
owner of the old bakery?

287
00:18:54,563 --> 00:18:56,980
Then get out of here right now, you brat.

288
00:18:57,105 --> 00:18:59,164
There's no reason for a father and son to stay
in the same place and die together, right?

289
00:18:59,188 --> 00:19:00,688
Are you threatening me?

290
00:19:00,813 --> 00:19:01,897
What threat?

291
00:19:02,022 --> 00:19:03,539
Who threatens someone by
offering them a huge pile of cash?

292
00:19:03,563 --> 00:19:05,123
And begging you to move?
You call that a threat?

293
00:19:05,147 --> 00:19:06,438
See that?

294
00:19:06,563 --> 00:19:10,563
My brother is a police officer.
I'm calling him right now.

295
00:19:13,938 --> 00:19:18,438
But Chairman, why are
we keeping them alive?

296
00:19:18,563 --> 00:19:21,272
In my opinion...

297
00:19:21,397 --> 00:19:25,037
Just like before, we should just make it look
like an accident and finish them off cleanly.

298
00:19:36,147 --> 00:19:37,206
This is your brother calling.

299
00:19:37,230 --> 00:19:41,938
If you run your mouth, everyone
here will die. Understand?

300
00:19:42,355 --> 00:19:43,105
Hyung?

301
00:19:43,230 --> 00:19:44,605
I'm a bit busy right now.

302
00:19:44,730 --> 00:19:47,813
I'll come over as soon
as I'm done. Don't worry.

303
00:19:47,938 --> 00:19:49,105
Hyung?

304
00:19:55,313 --> 00:19:56,938
What did he say?

305
00:19:57,938 --> 00:20:01,730
I've been a police officer on Earth
and lived a quiet life for a long time.

306
00:20:01,855 --> 00:20:04,206
I even received an award from the
Commissioner of the Police Agency.

307
00:20:04,230 --> 00:20:06,022
Secretary Lee.

308
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:08,320
Are we just going to
leave these people alone?

309
00:20:08,397 --> 00:20:10,813
Just do as the Chairman says.

310
00:20:11,688 --> 00:20:12,772
Sigh...

311
00:20:12,897 --> 00:20:17,522
If they run away, it's going
to be a headache for me.

312
00:20:17,647 --> 00:20:22,105
Forget it. The machine will
be activated soon anyway.

313
00:20:22,230 --> 00:20:24,105
We'll be leaving soon, too.

314
00:20:25,647 --> 00:20:27,022
That's true.

315
00:20:28,022 --> 00:20:29,730
Try calling again.

316
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:33,688
Hmm...

317
00:20:47,188 --> 00:20:50,272
This machine... I heard
it's very dangerous.

318
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:53,188
Is this machine really that dangerous?

319
00:20:53,855 --> 00:20:55,980
It won't cause any trouble yet.

320
00:20:57,938 --> 00:21:00,980
It will take a few more
days to fully activate.

321
00:21:01,091 --> 00:21:02,525
If this building really activates...

322
00:21:02,564 --> 00:21:06,398
Old man... can you stop
this machine now, please?

323
00:21:07,438 --> 00:21:10,397
It's beyond my control now.

324
00:21:10,522 --> 00:21:12,855
The building has
already started to activate.

325
00:21:14,563 --> 00:21:16,522
Is there really no way to stop it?

326
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:21,772
It's not entirely impossible.

327
00:21:22,897 --> 00:21:26,772
This harvester will extract the energy.

328
00:21:26,897 --> 00:21:29,873
Then it will concentrate that energy
and send it somewhere in the universe.

329
00:21:29,897 --> 00:21:33,522
So is someone else controlling
this building from somewhere else?

330
00:21:33,647 --> 00:21:35,397
I don't know where, either.

331
00:21:37,772 --> 00:21:40,605
Hachi, can you find out?

332
00:21:40,730 --> 00:21:43,605
This is where the landing
jammer was fired at our spaceship.

333
00:21:43,730 --> 00:21:46,188
Yes, and ship crashed because of it.

334
00:21:46,313 --> 00:21:49,355
It would be possible to track
down the location by tomorrow.

335
00:21:53,938 --> 00:21:56,688
I have one more thing to ask, Grandpa.

336
00:21:57,272 --> 00:21:59,063
About Wooju's father...

337
00:21:59,188 --> 00:22:00,897
How did he actually die?

338
00:22:03,063 --> 00:22:04,855
Did you kill him?

339
00:22:05,188 --> 00:22:06,480
That man...

340
00:22:06,605 --> 00:22:09,813
He wanted to destroy the energy
harvester the Chairman built.

341
00:22:09,938 --> 00:22:12,605
It was supposed to be a secret.
I don't know how he found out.

342
00:22:12,730 --> 00:22:16,938
He even damaged the
building, causing it to go dormant.

343
00:22:17,063 --> 00:22:23,188
I had no choice but to
tell the Chairman about it.

344
00:22:23,313 --> 00:22:26,522
I really wanted to go back home as well.

345
00:22:26,647 --> 00:22:28,188
You're a really bad person.

346
00:22:28,313 --> 00:22:30,605
That's right. It's the same as killing him.

347
00:22:30,730 --> 00:22:32,730
That's why I've always
felt so sorry about it.

348
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:39,147
Then why are you restarting this building?

349
00:22:39,272 --> 00:22:41,147
Because...

350
00:22:41,272 --> 00:22:43,980
Because of you, Your Highness.

351
00:22:44,563 --> 00:22:49,272
As long as you're in danger, the Royal Family
will definitely send someone to save you.

352
00:22:49,397 --> 00:22:52,522
Then the Chairman's
conspiracy will be exposed.

353
00:22:52,647 --> 00:22:53,647
You're crazy!

354
00:22:53,772 --> 00:22:55,605
Are you putting the
prince in danger for that?

355
00:22:55,730 --> 00:22:58,438
No one has ever come to save us.

356
00:22:58,563 --> 00:23:00,605
We've been living here
for over a hundred years.

357
00:23:00,730 --> 00:23:04,688
I really... I really want to see my family.

358
00:23:04,813 --> 00:23:06,688
I really miss them.

359
00:23:18,813 --> 00:23:21,063
Air, Air!

360
00:23:30,105 --> 00:23:32,397
Uh... Emperor?

361
00:23:32,605 --> 00:23:34,563
Air, come here! Quickly!

362
00:23:35,688 --> 00:23:36,855
What? What's happening?

363
00:23:36,980 --> 00:23:39,105
Air, salute!
